claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: Scatter plots with connected pre- and post-vaccination points showing the proportion of participants in two age groups (18–44 years and 45–64 years) who exhibited a ≥4-fold reduction in HI titer to cell-derived vaccine virus versus egg-derived virus for four influenza components (A(H3N2), A(H1N1)pdm09, B/VIC, B/YAM). Seven different Year 1–Year 2 vaccination sequences (ccIIV4, RIV4, IIV4, Fluzone combinations) are compared, with p-values indicating statistically significant changes between pre- and post-vaccination. does not support the claim because the figure presents immunogenicity (egg/cell HI titer ratios) across vaccine types and age groups, and does not provide any data on antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected strains. Note: None
